WEBVTT

00:00:58.664 --> 00:00:59.498
THIS IS A WORK OF FICTION

00:00:59.582 --> 00:01:01.083
CHILD ACTORS WERE FILMED SAFELY
WITH SUPERVISION

00:02:18.827 --> 00:02:20.412
Tell me, have you always flirted this way?

00:02:20.496 --> 00:02:22.957
[gasping]

00:02:24.541 --> 00:02:25.542
Are you insane?

00:02:32.883 --> 00:02:33.884
[sighs]

00:02:48.107 --> 00:02:49.483
No way.

00:02:54.196 --> 00:02:55.322
It can't be.

00:02:57.157 --> 00:02:58.158
Why?

00:02:58.242 --> 00:03:01.328
Why do I feel like Mr. Kang
would just let me get away with anything?

00:03:02.621 --> 00:03:03.914
Just one more drink together…

00:03:10.337 --> 00:03:12.256
Would you like to…

00:03:14.216 --> 00:03:15.050
[stammers]

00:03:15.134 --> 00:03:16.927
[Ji-yoon] …have another drink at my place?

00:03:18.387 --> 00:03:19.722
No, stop.

00:03:19.805 --> 00:03:21.306
Snap out of it, Cha Ji-yoon!

00:03:21.390 --> 00:03:25.269
Have me walk you home,
if you still have a long way?

00:03:27.646 --> 00:03:29.857
No, I'm only five minutes away.

00:03:29.940 --> 00:03:31.525
[sighs]

00:03:31.608 --> 00:03:32.443
Thank goodness.

00:03:34.361 --> 00:03:35.446
M-My place

00:03:35.529 --> 00:03:37.781
is right over there. Just right there.

00:03:40.701 --> 00:03:41.618
Have a good night.

00:03:46.206 --> 00:03:48.333
[sighing]

00:03:48.417 --> 00:03:50.544
Well done, Cha Ji-yoon. Well done.

00:03:51.837 --> 00:03:53.338
[sighs] The way I got out of that was…

00:03:54.590 --> 00:03:57.634
[groans] That was definitely
the best thing I did this year.

00:03:57.718 --> 00:04:01.680
[groans] With my superior?
I almost got involved with my superior.

00:04:02.639 --> 00:04:03.974
[sighs] That's just horrifying.

00:04:04.767 --> 00:04:06.143
[groans] So horrifying.

00:04:06.226 --> 00:04:07.853
Alcohol is my enemy.

00:04:07.936 --> 00:04:09.480
[sighs] It gives me strange dreams too.

00:04:09.563 --> 00:04:10.689
[groans]

00:04:11.648 --> 00:04:12.900
[sighs]

00:04:15.152 --> 00:04:16.236
[yelping]

00:04:35.464 --> 00:04:36.965
[groans]

00:04:37.049 --> 00:04:43.514
Not well done at all! [shrieks, groans]

00:04:44.264 --> 00:04:47.017
How am I gonna show my face
at work tomorrow? Damn it.

00:04:53.732 --> 00:04:55.234
[sighs]

00:04:55.317 --> 00:04:56.777
What are you doing tomorrow?

00:04:56.860 --> 00:04:58.112
If you're up for it,

00:04:58.195 --> 00:05:00.364
we should meet up again, okay?

00:05:00.989 --> 00:05:02.741
Would you like to…

00:05:04.785 --> 00:05:08.580
Have me walk you home,
if you still have a long way?

00:05:09.665 --> 00:05:10.582
Have a good night.

00:05:10.666 --> 00:05:14.878
[pop music plays]

00:05:16.713 --> 00:05:17.673
Was that a no?

00:05:22.594 --> 00:05:24.054
[sighs]

00:05:25.305 --> 00:05:26.849
[sighs] Here it is.

00:05:30.144 --> 00:05:31.145
Here. [sighs]

00:05:38.318 --> 00:05:40.028
Buy two and get a free one? Of course.

00:05:40.112 --> 00:05:41.405
BUTTER COCONUT BISCUIT

00:05:47.494 --> 00:05:49.163
-[chuckles] Hello.
-Mmm.

00:05:50.664 --> 00:05:51.832
Did you have a rough night?

00:05:51.915 --> 00:05:52.958
Yes.

00:05:55.794 --> 00:05:57.713
[moans]

00:05:57.796 --> 00:05:59.006
Oh, that's better.

00:05:59.798 --> 00:06:00.924
[sighs]

00:06:01.967 --> 00:06:03.302
That'll be 18.06.

00:06:03.385 --> 00:06:04.344
Just a moment.

00:06:09.183 --> 00:06:10.058
Hello.

00:06:11.018 --> 00:06:12.269
That'll be 1.20.

00:06:15.147 --> 00:06:16.190
Ms. Cha Ji-yoon?

00:06:19.693 --> 00:06:20.569
[Ji-yoon] Is this

00:06:21.278 --> 00:06:22.404
for real?

00:06:28.535 --> 00:06:29.578
Uh…

00:06:30.537 --> 00:06:33.457
I came out in a hurry, so…

00:06:39.588 --> 00:06:41.506
I see you bought a lot of snacks.

00:06:41.590 --> 00:06:42.633
Oh, yes.

00:06:50.515 --> 00:06:51.683
Would you like a popsicle?

00:06:56.647 --> 00:06:57.814
Oh.

00:06:57.898 --> 00:07:00.108
If you don't like this,
how about chocolate--

00:07:18.210 --> 00:07:19.920
That'll be 20.83.

00:07:21.338 --> 00:07:23.840
Huh? He paid for this and didn't take it.

00:07:25.592 --> 00:07:27.844
-You know him, right? That guy.
-Sorry?

00:07:28.929 --> 00:07:29.763
Me?

00:07:37.479 --> 00:07:41.441
[chuckling]

00:07:42.109 --> 00:07:44.319
[sighs]

00:07:55.998 --> 00:07:57.165
Look, Mom, that lady's

00:07:57.249 --> 00:08:00.460
wearing undies
and they look just like Dad's.

00:08:01.962 --> 00:08:04.923
No, I'm not. These are silk shorts.
I bought them in Thailand.

00:08:05.007 --> 00:08:06.425
-[parent] I'm sorry.
-[chuckles]

00:08:06.508 --> 00:08:07.592
[parent] They look nice.

00:08:09.720 --> 00:08:12.889
[chuckling]

00:08:15.600 --> 00:08:17.352
[Ji-yoon] Hmm? Is he… is he laughing?

00:08:18.562 --> 00:08:19.730
Three-No-Man

00:08:20.439 --> 00:08:22.149
is actually laughing at me?

00:08:26.611 --> 00:08:28.989
[chuckling continues]

00:08:29.072 --> 00:08:30.365
I'm going to quit!

00:08:34.536 --> 00:08:40.208
EPISODE 2
DREAMING OF QUITTING, STILL CLOCKING IN!

00:08:42.502 --> 00:08:44.212
[sighs]

00:08:45.213 --> 00:08:47.132
He'd still go to work
even if he was fired.

00:08:50.052 --> 00:08:51.887
[sighs]

00:08:51.970 --> 00:08:55.474
So, what, you gonna hand him this
and say hi to his face?

00:08:57.642 --> 00:08:59.186
[sighs]

00:08:59.269 --> 00:09:01.480
[voicemail] The person you are calling
is unavailable.

00:09:01.563 --> 00:09:03.273
You'll be redirected to voicemail.

00:09:04.232 --> 00:09:05.942
Your boyfriend's been a bit quiet lately.

00:09:06.610 --> 00:09:09.112
He used to call at lunchtime
like clockwork.

00:09:09.196 --> 00:09:10.322
[chuckles]

00:09:10.405 --> 00:09:12.366
He gets like this
when he's too into an experiment

00:09:12.449 --> 00:09:15.452
[groans] I hate even thinking about it.
Experiments.

00:09:18.789 --> 00:09:20.999
No-ah, I'm going to run to the restroom,
okay?

00:09:21.750 --> 00:09:22.626
[No-ah] What?

00:09:28.215 --> 00:09:31.593
Oh. Bulgogi combo.
Man, looks like you took all the bulgogi.

00:09:32.260 --> 00:09:34.137
Enjoy your meal. Yeah. You too.

00:09:34.846 --> 00:09:36.932
Why is it that you
never eat with your own team?

00:09:37.015 --> 00:09:39.393
Well, you know,
there's a deep purpose behind that.

00:09:39.476 --> 00:09:42.145
He's always hunting for a scoop
even while he's eating.

00:09:42.229 --> 00:09:44.606
[chuckles] Old-fashioned intel gathering.

00:09:45.232 --> 00:09:47.401
So, are there any new scoops these days?

00:09:47.484 --> 00:09:49.361
Anything more shocking than Three-No-Man

00:09:49.444 --> 00:09:50.404
becoming our team lead?

00:09:50.487 --> 00:09:52.364
[chuckles] You're right.

00:09:52.447 --> 00:09:54.282
What's he like to work with?
Are the rumors true?

00:09:54.366 --> 00:09:56.451
Not only are the rumors true
about the three No's,

00:09:56.535 --> 00:09:59.204
but he’s also a huge workaholic.

00:09:59.287 --> 00:10:01.373
-Hasn’t he got a place yet?
-Why?

00:10:01.456 --> 00:10:03.750
No one's seen him arrive or even leave.

00:10:03.834 --> 00:10:04.793
He's always just here.

00:10:05.544 --> 00:10:06.711
Just like he's built-in furniture.

00:10:08.630 --> 00:10:10.715
The total opposite of our team lead.

00:10:10.799 --> 00:10:12.968
We never see Mr. Ko stay at his desk.

00:10:13.802 --> 00:10:14.678
That's right.

00:10:15.762 --> 00:10:18.849
-Did you hear about their backstory?
-No.

00:10:19.516 --> 00:10:21.435
I heard this through the Secretarial Team.

00:10:22.269 --> 00:10:24.146
Mr. Kang was actually with Development,

00:10:24.229 --> 00:10:27.315
before briefly moving to Product Planning
to work under Mr. Ko.

00:10:27.399 --> 00:10:28.525
-Really?
-Hmm.

00:10:28.608 --> 00:10:30.735
Get this, Kang Si-woo was a Sr. Associate,

00:10:30.819 --> 00:10:34.156
and he reported his team lead,
Mr. Ko, for taking bribes.

00:10:34.239 --> 00:10:35.157
[gasps]

00:10:35.240 --> 00:10:36.616
[whispers]
Just so he could take that spot.

00:10:37.367 --> 00:10:38.201
What?

00:10:38.285 --> 00:10:42.289
Whoa. So that's the reason
Mr. Ko hates Mr. Kang.

00:10:42.956 --> 00:10:44.332
He really is the Grim Reaper.

00:10:44.416 --> 00:10:46.293
[Kee-tae] He's a total snake that guy.

00:10:46.376 --> 00:10:47.711
[No-ah, chuckles] Seriously.

00:10:47.794 --> 00:10:51.173
-Hey, keep eating. Keep eating.
-[No-ah clears throat]

00:10:51.256 --> 00:10:52.382
[rock music plays]

00:10:52.466 --> 00:10:56.887
-[employee 1] Mr. Kang Si-woo?
-[employee 2] I thought he eats alone.

00:11:05.604 --> 00:11:06.605
May I join you for lunch?

00:11:06.688 --> 00:11:07.689
Please take this seat.

00:11:09.524 --> 00:11:10.775
-Right here.
-Stop it.

00:11:27.042 --> 00:11:29.169
That is a severely unbalanced meal,
you know.

00:11:29.794 --> 00:11:32.297
And I noticed you make your coffee
with two sticks.

00:11:32.380 --> 00:11:33.924
That’s damaging to your health.

00:11:37.177 --> 00:11:40.472
Oh. [chuckles]

00:11:40.555 --> 00:11:42.641
I see you have no rice at all.

00:11:43.475 --> 00:11:45.894
Yes, I’d hate to gain belly fat.

00:11:47.103 --> 00:11:48.188
[yelping]

00:11:51.566 --> 00:11:54.569
[coughing]

00:12:00.116 --> 00:12:01.993
You all get coffee after lunch, right?

00:12:02.869 --> 00:12:03.828
Well, it's on me today.

00:12:04.579 --> 00:12:06.665
-Re-Really?
-Ms. Cha, you should--

00:12:06.748 --> 00:12:08.583
I forgot I had something urgent
to take care of,

00:12:08.667 --> 00:12:10.669
I apologize.
I will see you all later though.

00:12:15.715 --> 00:12:17.050
If you’ll excuse me too.

00:12:21.137 --> 00:12:22.806
[Ji-yoon] That scared the hell out of me.

00:12:23.348 --> 00:12:24.182
Me too.

00:12:24.266 --> 00:12:27.185
He always eats alone.
So why did he decide to sit with us then?

00:12:27.269 --> 00:12:28.770
He was acting all buddy-buddy
talking to you.

00:12:28.853 --> 00:12:29.938
I know, right?

00:12:31.731 --> 00:12:33.858
I'll have an Iced Americano. And you?

00:12:35.318 --> 00:12:36.444
I'll have

00:12:36.528 --> 00:12:38.238
a chocolate mocha smoothie please.

00:12:38.863 --> 00:12:42.617
We'll have one iced Americano
and one chocolate mocha smoothie, please.

00:12:42.701 --> 00:12:43.618
Hey.

00:12:43.702 --> 00:12:45.245
I'm paying this time though.

00:12:46.162 --> 00:12:48.790
-[Si-woo] We'll pay with this card.
-Sure. Please tap it here.

00:12:48.873 --> 00:12:49.708
KANG SI-WOO

00:12:50.333 --> 00:12:52.669
I thought you had something urgent
to take care of?

00:12:52.752 --> 00:12:53.712
I guess you meant coffee.

00:12:55.005 --> 00:12:57.632
I was in desperate need
of a caffeine transfusion.

00:12:57.716 --> 00:12:59.467
Then, while you get your caffeine fix…

00:13:00.135 --> 00:13:01.303
shall we have a chat?

00:13:01.386 --> 00:13:04.264
Oh, I left something in the cafeteria.

00:13:04.347 --> 00:13:05.974
No-ah, would you grab my coffee?

00:13:06.683 --> 00:13:08.935
Wait, but you didn't bring
anything with you.

00:13:14.065 --> 00:13:14.941
Thank you.

00:13:16.776 --> 00:13:20.780
-What's going on?
-What do you mean?

00:13:20.864 --> 00:13:22.824
There's something between
you and Mr. Kang.

00:13:22.907 --> 00:13:24.826
[sighs] There's nothing going on.

00:13:25.410 --> 00:13:26.536
I guess he's figured it out too.

00:13:26.620 --> 00:13:27.579
What?

00:13:27.662 --> 00:13:28.997
That you're great at your job.

00:13:29.080 --> 00:13:31.207
Isn't he trying to get you
to do some work for him?

00:13:31.875 --> 00:13:34.085
We're on different teams.
He can't assign work to me.

00:13:34.169 --> 00:13:36.463
Then what? Maybe he just likes you.

00:13:37.047 --> 00:13:38.340
That's even more unlikely.

00:13:38.423 --> 00:13:42.302
If that's not it, then why is he
following you around like that?

00:13:52.937 --> 00:13:54.648
So, did you find the thing you lost?

00:13:54.731 --> 00:13:55.565
Yes.

00:13:56.274 --> 00:13:58.401
Then, are you free this evening?

00:13:58.485 --> 00:13:59.444
Yes.

00:13:59.527 --> 00:14:00.528
No!

00:14:00.612 --> 00:14:02.739
I have plans that I cannot cancel.

00:14:02.822 --> 00:14:04.032
I figured as much.

00:14:11.581 --> 00:14:14.084
I told you. He wants to see you
this evening.

00:14:14.167 --> 00:14:15.669
You know what this is?

00:14:15.752 --> 00:14:17.962
It’s like, when you happen to
see someone’s weakness,

00:14:18.046 --> 00:14:20.590
you develop this one-sided sense
of closeness with them, that’s all.

00:14:20.674 --> 00:14:21.925
Sorry?

00:14:22.008 --> 00:14:24.386
He's just doing it
because he thinks I'm a pushover.

00:14:25.303 --> 00:14:26.429
Let's go.

00:14:37.399 --> 00:14:38.441
[Hye-ji] Hey!

00:14:38.525 --> 00:14:39.651
Lee Hye-ji!

00:14:40.402 --> 00:14:41.403
Lee Hye-ji!

00:14:41.486 --> 00:14:43.113
[chuckles] It’s been far too long!

00:14:43.196 --> 00:14:45.031
Did you miss me a lot or what?

00:14:45.115 --> 00:14:46.116
Not at all.

00:14:46.866 --> 00:14:49.619
Do you know how long it's been
since I've left the house with a purse

00:14:49.703 --> 00:14:51.788
and no diaper bag? It's been far too long.

00:14:52.580 --> 00:14:56.418
Hey, all that spicy food I had to avoid
while breastfeeding?

00:14:56.501 --> 00:14:57.919
I’m going to eat it all today.

00:14:58.002 --> 00:14:59.045
All right.

00:14:59.129 --> 00:15:00.422
Let's eat it all!

00:15:00.505 --> 00:15:02.966
-[chuckles]
-Let's go. Right this way.

00:15:03.049 --> 00:15:04.426
I'm so excited for today.

00:15:08.513 --> 00:15:11.266
Do you have any guesses
as to why he wants to see you?

00:15:11.349 --> 00:15:12.434
No idea.

00:15:12.517 --> 00:15:15.937
Oh. Maybe he wants to make sure
I keep my mouth shut before he leaves.

00:15:16.020 --> 00:15:17.021
He's leaving?

00:15:17.105 --> 00:15:18.481
Looks like it.

00:15:18.565 --> 00:15:20.358
What do you mean, "keep your mouth shut"?

00:15:20.442 --> 00:15:21.609
You see,

00:15:22.527 --> 00:15:25.947
I kind of accidentally stumbled
onto a really private secret of his.

00:15:26.030 --> 00:15:29.743
Meaning he was busted
with a very private secret by you.

00:15:29.826 --> 00:15:30.869
Mm-hmm.

00:15:30.952 --> 00:15:33.538
And he caught you looking like
a total mess, the kind you

00:15:33.621 --> 00:15:34.956
pray no one ever witnesses?

00:15:35.039 --> 00:15:36.958
-Hmm.
-And now he’s leaving the company?

00:15:37.542 --> 00:15:38.752
Hmm, to put it simply.

00:15:38.835 --> 00:15:41.629
The way I see it, this is…

00:15:42.839 --> 00:15:44.090
the perfect lead to a confession.

00:15:44.174 --> 00:15:45.550
What?

00:15:45.633 --> 00:15:47.469
You said he laughed
because of what you were wearing.

00:15:47.552 --> 00:15:50.764
You also said, he’s the kind of person…
who never laughs

00:15:50.847 --> 00:15:54.350
That means you completely made him
let his guard down.

00:15:55.185 --> 00:15:57.020
And now that he’s leaving the company,

00:15:57.520 --> 00:16:00.899
there’s no need to worry about getting
caught. He’s gonna ask you out.

00:16:00.982 --> 00:16:04.110
I know… but you’re only saying that
because you don’t know him.

00:16:04.194 --> 00:16:06.738
That kind of language
doesn’t suit him at all.

00:16:07.322 --> 00:16:08.406
You know the type.

00:16:08.490 --> 00:16:12.494
He’s the kind of person who always seems
to have a storm cloud over his head.

00:16:12.577 --> 00:16:15.872
Better than a guy who’s like… [giggles]
…and who’s all sunshine and flowers.

00:16:15.955 --> 00:16:19.125
-[scoffs]
-Just go for it.

00:16:19.209 --> 00:16:21.252
Go see if there’s any chemistry there.
Hmm?

00:16:21.336 --> 00:16:22.921
If there's no major red flag.

00:16:23.421 --> 00:16:25.173
Hey, you get over one man
with another man.

00:16:25.256 --> 00:16:26.883
You're wrong about that.

00:16:26.966 --> 00:16:29.594
You do it with fried chicken,
beer and going to work.

00:16:29.677 --> 00:16:32.639
[sighs] Imagine having all that
and going to work together.

00:16:32.722 --> 00:16:33.973
How fun would that be?

00:16:34.557 --> 00:16:37.101
Stop with the nonsense and just eat this.
Open up.

00:16:37.185 --> 00:16:38.186
NEVER-DIE CHICKEN FEET

00:16:38.269 --> 00:16:39.604
[laughing]

00:16:42.148 --> 00:16:43.149
[groans]

00:16:45.527 --> 00:16:46.402
Gosh, that's spicy.

00:16:49.864 --> 00:16:53.243
[electrical humming]

00:16:58.998 --> 00:17:02.126
Mr. Kang, looks like
you had a relaxed commute.

00:17:02.710 --> 00:17:03.837
Yes.

00:17:03.920 --> 00:17:06.172
The urgent work I had to deal with
has settled down for now.

00:17:06.256 --> 00:17:08.383
Oh. That's good.

00:17:09.884 --> 00:17:12.387
It looks like me coming in early

00:17:12.470 --> 00:17:14.097
made things difficult for you.

00:17:14.180 --> 00:17:16.057
[scoffs] How could you think that?

00:17:16.140 --> 00:17:19.102
How could I think that?
I always come to work on time, and…

00:17:19.185 --> 00:17:20.728
-[automated voice] Doors opening.
-Oh, elevator's here.

00:17:32.198 --> 00:17:33.908
Please, get in.

00:17:35.827 --> 00:17:38.621
[Hye-ji] The way I see it, this is…

00:17:39.247 --> 00:17:41.124
the perfect lead to a confession.

00:17:42.000 --> 00:17:44.669
Oh, I left something
at the security checkpoint.

00:17:44.752 --> 00:17:45.670
Please go ahead.

00:17:46.838 --> 00:17:48.673
Can you even leave stuff at security?

00:17:53.219 --> 00:17:55.847
[sighs] Seriously?

00:17:55.930 --> 00:17:58.391
Why did Hye-ji have to go and say that?

00:17:58.474 --> 00:18:00.560
Geez. It's all I think about.

00:18:02.020 --> 00:18:03.354
[sighs]

00:18:04.606 --> 00:18:05.607
That girl has been

00:18:06.816 --> 00:18:07.817
pretty scatterbrained lately.

00:18:08.776 --> 00:18:11.362
Weren't you and Ms. Cha
hired at the same time?

00:18:11.446 --> 00:18:12.947
Yeah. Oh, my apologies.

00:18:13.990 --> 00:18:17.035
Cha Ji-yoon was the first person
in our group promoted to Sr. Associate.

00:18:17.702 --> 00:18:20.830
Of course, I do feel
like I'm a bit behind, truly.

00:18:22.248 --> 00:18:24.918
I've noticed you have lunch together.
Are you close?

00:18:25.501 --> 00:18:27.837
Yes, she's the one
I get along the best with.

00:18:29.839 --> 00:18:30.924
That's good.

00:18:31.507 --> 00:18:33.384
Wh-What exactly is good?

00:18:51.903 --> 00:18:53.279
-Hey.
-Hey.

00:18:53.363 --> 00:18:55.198
I told you to wait.
Why are you drinking alone?

00:18:55.281 --> 00:18:57.575
Oh… [chuckles]

00:18:58.493 --> 00:18:59.369
Give me that.

00:19:02.246 --> 00:19:03.498
Hey, hey.

00:19:04.374 --> 00:19:05.541
As you already know,

00:19:06.417 --> 00:19:10.129
I graduated from a rural college,
so I didn’t have hometown connections.

00:19:10.213 --> 00:19:13.549
That's right. How impressive is that, huh?

00:19:13.633 --> 00:19:16.803
You don't have any of that
and yet you're doing so well at work.

00:19:18.972 --> 00:19:21.224
If I'm doing great,
why haven't I made Sr. Associate?

00:19:22.058 --> 00:19:23.226
Hey.

00:19:23.935 --> 00:19:25.812
That's because

00:19:25.895 --> 00:19:29.232
you've just had terrible luck
with bosses so far.

00:19:30.233 --> 00:19:31.234
At this rate,

00:19:32.235 --> 00:19:33.528
I'm not sure I can raise

00:19:35.071 --> 00:19:36.197
Gyeol and Yul right.

00:19:36.280 --> 00:19:38.491
And if you decide to quit then what?

00:19:38.574 --> 00:19:40.368
You need to have another job lined up

00:19:40.451 --> 00:19:42.286
before you decide
to make a move like that.

00:19:42.370 --> 00:19:43.371
Hmm.

00:19:44.998 --> 00:19:46.874
That's why I'm trying to find
a new way in.

00:19:46.958 --> 00:19:47.792
What?

00:19:47.875 --> 00:19:48.918
He's here.

00:19:51.462 --> 00:19:53.506
My new lifeline.

00:19:54.340 --> 00:19:57.385
[clears throat] Gosh.

00:19:57.468 --> 00:19:59.804
What a coincidence
running into you again like this.

00:19:59.887 --> 00:20:01.180
-[phone buzzing]
-Oh, gosh. What's this.

00:20:01.264 --> 00:20:03.099
Goodness.
You two should go ahead and talk.

00:20:03.182 --> 00:20:04.934
I gotta take this call. Yes.

00:20:05.018 --> 00:20:06.644
My wife sweet is calling so--

00:20:06.728 --> 00:20:07.562
What are you doing right now?

00:20:07.645 --> 00:20:09.480
What are colleagues for?
Please help me. Please!

00:20:12.859 --> 00:20:14.193
Your timing is impeccable.

00:20:21.826 --> 00:20:24.912
[Ji-yoon] He even used my colleague
so he could see me alone?

00:20:24.996 --> 00:20:26.831
Trying to get you alone has proven to be,

00:20:27.623 --> 00:20:28.833
quite the challenge.

00:20:28.916 --> 00:20:29.751
[Ji-yoon] Alone?

00:20:30.585 --> 00:20:31.836
Why alone?

00:20:31.919 --> 00:20:34.130
Did you have something to say to me?

00:20:34.213 --> 00:20:35.506
Yes.

00:20:36.340 --> 00:20:37.925
There's something I need to say.

00:20:38.009 --> 00:20:39.093
[Ji-yoon] What should I do?

00:20:42.180 --> 00:20:43.306
Is here okay?

00:20:44.682 --> 00:20:46.434
We can go elsewhere if you'd prefer.

00:20:46.517 --> 00:20:48.394
Oh, no. This is fine.

00:20:48.978 --> 00:20:50.104
Please, go ahead.

00:20:51.397 --> 00:20:52.648
Ms. Cha Ji-yoon, I think

00:20:53.608 --> 00:20:54.484
I like you.

00:20:54.567 --> 00:20:55.860
I like you.

00:20:55.943 --> 00:20:57.070
I like you.

00:20:57.153 --> 00:20:58.905
[Ji-yoon] Is he about to confess?

00:20:58.988 --> 00:21:02.283
So, Ms. Cha, I’d like you to… go…

00:21:03.493 --> 00:21:04.827
[Ji-yoon] Go…

00:21:06.537 --> 00:21:09.499
out…

00:21:10.124 --> 00:21:12.710
…to go work with me on a task
assigned by the President.

00:21:13.753 --> 00:21:14.670
What?

00:21:14.754 --> 00:21:18.341
The ice sphere refrigerator
is going back into development.

00:21:18.424 --> 00:21:20.426
I'd like you to be on the team.

00:21:24.764 --> 00:21:26.390
[spoon clatters]

00:21:27.475 --> 00:21:28.434
Oh. No, no, no. Please.

00:21:28.518 --> 00:21:30.186
I got it. Let me.

00:21:33.523 --> 00:21:35.900
I wish I could disappear right now.

00:21:40.363 --> 00:21:41.572
Thank you.

00:21:48.037 --> 00:21:51.874
So when you said you had gotten fired…

00:21:51.958 --> 00:21:53.626
I got fired from Planning Team 2.

00:21:53.709 --> 00:21:54.544
So…

00:21:55.086 --> 00:21:56.295
when you suggested

00:21:57.046 --> 00:21:58.506
we get a drink last weekend…

00:21:58.589 --> 00:22:00.550
I couldn't bring it up
because you were too drunk.

00:22:00.633 --> 00:22:01.843
So the reason you kept

00:22:01.926 --> 00:22:04.720
following me around these past few days…

00:22:04.804 --> 00:22:06.597
You didn't give me
much of a chance to tell you.

00:22:09.517 --> 00:22:10.726
[Ji-yoon] It's so mortifying

00:22:11.519 --> 00:22:13.146
that it was all in my head, but…

00:22:16.315 --> 00:22:17.233
What a relief.

00:22:17.942 --> 00:22:19.652
I really appreciate the offer,

00:22:20.278 --> 00:22:23.823
but at this time, I have no intention
of switching teams.

00:22:23.906 --> 00:22:25.867
May I ask you why that is?

00:22:25.950 --> 00:22:28.244
There are some issues
with the voice-activated water dispenser

00:22:28.327 --> 00:22:29.745
that I'm working on.

00:22:30.329 --> 00:22:32.123
I'd really like to

00:22:32.206 --> 00:22:34.542
get everything resolved and see it
launched successfully this year.

00:22:34.625 --> 00:22:35.877
If that's your reason,

00:22:35.960 --> 00:22:38.588
I'll let you stay in the loop just until
you're all done with the launch.

00:22:38.671 --> 00:22:40.006
Oh, no.

00:22:40.882 --> 00:22:43.926
Hmm, if I'm being perfectly honest, I'm…

00:22:45.178 --> 00:22:46.721
I'm scared of failing right now.

00:22:48.848 --> 00:22:51.100
I’d like to work on something
with better chances.

00:22:54.228 --> 00:22:56.022
You went to such trouble to bring this up,

00:22:56.856 --> 00:22:57.940
I'm really sorry.

00:22:59.901 --> 00:23:00.860
I understand.

00:23:02.069 --> 00:23:05.072
Do me a favor and keep this between us,
until they announce it.

00:23:05.156 --> 00:23:05.990
Sure.

00:23:07.241 --> 00:23:08.326
[Kee-tae] Oh, my gosh.

00:23:08.409 --> 00:23:10.995
Oh, my goodness. Oh, my goodness.
I'm so sorry. I brought these.

00:23:11.078 --> 00:23:13.873
[chuckles] Here. New ones.

00:23:17.084 --> 00:23:19.629
-Mr. Kang, can I pour you a drink?
-Sure.

00:23:21.714 --> 00:23:23.758
By the way, there’s something
I’ve been wanting to ask you.

00:23:23.841 --> 00:23:25.009
All right, I'm listening.

00:23:25.092 --> 00:23:27.053
Do you happen to know
about your nickname yet?

00:23:27.136 --> 00:23:28.012
Hey.

00:23:29.388 --> 00:23:30.223
Are you drunk?

00:23:30.890 --> 00:23:31.724
No.

00:23:31.807 --> 00:23:33.184
"Three-No-Man," is that right?

00:23:33.893 --> 00:23:34.852
So you knew about it.

00:23:34.936 --> 00:23:37.313
"No smiles, no people, no apologies."

00:23:37.396 --> 00:23:40.233
Whoever came up with that
did a pretty good job if you ask me.

00:23:42.443 --> 00:23:43.444
[whispering] So he knew?

00:23:46.072 --> 00:23:48.950
Enjoy your drinks
and please use this to pay.

00:23:49.033 --> 00:23:50.368
Y-You're already leaving?

00:23:50.451 --> 00:23:51.285
Yes.

00:23:52.245 --> 00:23:53.537
We had a good talk thanks to you.

00:23:54.455 --> 00:23:55.331
See you tomorrow.

00:23:56.165 --> 00:23:57.416
[Kee-tae] Wait.

00:23:57.500 --> 00:23:59.252
Right. Oh. Uh…

00:23:59.335 --> 00:24:01.045
Have a… Have a safe trip home then.

00:24:03.047 --> 00:24:04.048
Man.

00:24:04.715 --> 00:24:08.219
How dare you use work as an excuse
to get me here?

00:24:08.302 --> 00:24:10.096
I mean, what choice did I have.
He said he wanted to see you.

00:24:10.179 --> 00:24:12.265
[groans] That really hurt.

00:24:13.391 --> 00:24:15.309
Hey, so what did you guys talk about, huh?

00:24:15.393 --> 00:24:17.019
It's classified, you punk. [clicks tongue]

00:24:18.187 --> 00:24:19.313
"Classified"?

00:24:19.397 --> 00:24:21.440
[soft pop music plays]

00:24:43.421 --> 00:24:45.047
YEONG-MOOK REPAIR SERVICES

00:25:02.356 --> 00:25:03.524
Hi.

00:25:05.443 --> 00:25:07.278
-When did you get back?
-A few days ago.

00:25:07.361 --> 00:25:08.612
[Yeong-mook chuckles]

00:25:08.696 --> 00:25:11.907
I really thought you weren't
coming back ever again.

00:25:16.329 --> 00:25:18.873
-What's this?
-I found it on the way here.

00:25:26.255 --> 00:25:27.590
Huh, this is…

00:25:31.927 --> 00:25:32.928
My goodness.

00:25:35.348 --> 00:25:37.975
Well, I’ll need to work
another ten years to earn this.

00:25:38.059 --> 00:25:39.643
I'll find you another one
in ten years time.

00:25:39.727 --> 00:25:42.229
[chuckles]

00:25:44.565 --> 00:25:46.400
Thanks so much.

00:25:52.365 --> 00:25:55.618
[peaceful music plays]

00:25:58.204 --> 00:26:01.290
[sighs, clicks tongue]

00:26:02.166 --> 00:26:03.376
[sighs]

00:26:03.459 --> 00:26:07.046
Like I thought. No matter where I go
there’s nothing like your sound system.

00:26:07.129 --> 00:26:08.672
There’s nothing special about it.

00:26:10.716 --> 00:26:13.469
It's just a bunch of broken parts
that I slapped together.

00:26:13.552 --> 00:26:14.553
I like it.

00:26:15.096 --> 00:26:16.889
I like that sound in this shop.

00:26:18.432 --> 00:26:19.809
I always feel at ease

00:26:20.976 --> 00:26:22.144
whenever I come here.

00:26:22.228 --> 00:26:23.604
What is going on now?

00:26:25.231 --> 00:26:27.775
-Something not going your way?
-How did you know that?

00:26:27.858 --> 00:26:29.652
You wouldn't be here for any other reason.

00:26:29.735 --> 00:26:31.737
[both chuckle]

00:26:40.538 --> 00:26:42.456
There's a mountain of stuff to repair,

00:26:43.916 --> 00:26:47.086
get your hands moving
and try to get your thoughts in order.

00:26:52.550 --> 00:26:53.926
[sighs]

00:27:08.607 --> 00:27:10.734
Wow, this one looks far too difficult.

00:27:10.818 --> 00:27:13.320
You need to try the hard ones
if you want to improve.

00:27:20.411 --> 00:27:21.912
Your hands have really slowed down.

00:27:22.538 --> 00:27:23.414
Hand that over.

00:27:23.497 --> 00:27:24.623
Hey, hey. Come on now.

00:27:25.499 --> 00:27:26.625
Work on your own thing.

00:27:26.709 --> 00:27:29.003
I like things with clear solutions.
[chuckles]

00:27:31.088 --> 00:27:33.924
And that is the reason
why you're so bad at dating.

00:27:34.008 --> 00:27:35.676
Wow, hitting me where it hurts.

00:27:36.427 --> 00:27:38.012
I’m actually on my way back
from getting rejected.

00:27:38.095 --> 00:27:39.680
Oh…

00:27:39.763 --> 00:27:41.015
Have you taken an interest in someone?

00:27:41.098 --> 00:27:43.976
Just give me some advice
on what I should do exactly.

00:27:44.059 --> 00:27:45.853
What advice is there to give?

00:27:46.645 --> 00:27:49.857
Either drop it and move on,
or keep pushing until it works out.

00:27:51.692 --> 00:27:52.526
Is she pretty?

00:27:52.610 --> 00:27:55.070
-[scoffs]
-[laughs]

00:27:55.571 --> 00:27:56.489
That's good.

00:27:57.323 --> 00:28:00.034
Hey, smile like that more often.

00:28:00.951 --> 00:28:03.621
[sighs] You live long enough…

00:28:03.704 --> 00:28:05.748
you realize how precious smiling days are.

00:28:37.738 --> 00:28:40.115
Huh? Hey, a task force notice is up!

00:28:40.199 --> 00:28:41.992
[employee 1] Huh?

00:28:42.076 --> 00:28:43.494
What kind of task force?

00:28:43.577 --> 00:28:45.538
TASK FORCE: A TEMPORARY TEAM
FORMED FOR A SPECIFIC PROJECT

00:28:45.621 --> 00:28:47.289
Pretty random timing for a task force.

00:28:47.373 --> 00:28:48.749
RECRUITMENT - FUTURE STRATEGY TASK FORCE

00:28:48.832 --> 00:28:49.959
Manager Kang Si-woo?

00:28:50.918 --> 00:28:53.671
[Ji-yoon] So this is what Mr. Kang
was talking about.

00:28:53.754 --> 00:28:56.757
He just became team lead for Team 2,
and he's already leading a task force?

00:29:01.262 --> 00:29:02.263
That was it?

00:29:02.346 --> 00:29:03.847
Is that why he asked to see you?

00:29:04.682 --> 00:29:06.058
-Mm-hmm.
-Are you going to?

00:29:06.141 --> 00:29:07.434
I'm not.

00:29:07.518 --> 00:29:08.644
[sighs] Thank goodness.

00:29:09.144 --> 00:29:10.563
Gosh, I was terrified
at the thought of you

00:29:10.646 --> 00:29:12.314
being forced into a hellhole 'cause of me.

00:29:12.398 --> 00:29:13.440
What's going on?

00:29:13.524 --> 00:29:14.817
Don't just keep it between yourselves.

00:29:14.900 --> 00:29:16.610
Spill the beans.
What exactly is happening?

00:29:22.032 --> 00:29:24.118
We all assumed that Mr. Kang was done for

00:29:24.868 --> 00:29:27.913
after halting operations
of the ice sphere fridge

00:29:27.997 --> 00:29:29.331
-did we not?
-That's right.

00:29:29.415 --> 00:29:31.125
But, that was not the case.

00:29:32.293 --> 00:29:33.627
Just as I thought, Mr. Kang Si-woo,

00:29:35.254 --> 00:29:38.382
I don't think your current position
is right for you at all.

00:29:39.883 --> 00:29:42.678
You should step down
as the team lead of Product Planning.

00:29:45.639 --> 00:29:46.640
As you suggested,

00:29:47.433 --> 00:29:49.977
we will completely suspend
the ice sphere refrigerator project.

00:29:50.060 --> 00:29:51.061
Instead,

00:29:51.145 --> 00:29:55.274
I want you to form a task force and start
developing the fridge from scratch.

00:29:55.899 --> 00:29:59.820
Then, I'd like full authority
and responsibility of every step,

00:29:59.903 --> 00:30:02.364
from planning all the way to final launch.

00:30:02.448 --> 00:30:05.117
Also, I will report directly to you.

00:30:06.452 --> 00:30:07.453
Agreed.

00:30:10.205 --> 00:30:11.832
Wow, that's crazy.

00:30:11.915 --> 00:30:13.459
[employee] Straight to the president?

00:30:14.376 --> 00:30:17.338
I mean, just how much faith
does the President have in Mr. Kang

00:30:17.421 --> 00:30:18.547
to back him this hard?

00:30:18.631 --> 00:30:21.050
It's President Han. You know that.

00:30:21.133 --> 00:30:24.261
She's a self-made legend who started
as a regular employee

00:30:24.345 --> 00:30:26.138
and made it all the way to President.

00:30:26.221 --> 00:30:27.556
She knows better than anyone

00:30:27.640 --> 00:30:31.060
what the working-level staff struggle
with, namely, that rigid hierarchy.

00:30:32.728 --> 00:30:34.688
And Mr. Kang picked up on that exactly.

00:30:34.772 --> 00:30:36.857
[sighs] Okay.

00:30:36.940 --> 00:30:39.568
But taking on a project
that's been suspended before…

00:30:40.152 --> 00:30:41.445
Is that a step up or step down?

00:30:41.528 --> 00:30:46.617
That, right there is exactly the core
of this… change.

00:30:47.785 --> 00:30:50.829
Question is,
did she just give Mr. Kang wings to fly,

00:30:50.913 --> 00:30:52.289
or did she set a trap for him?

00:30:52.373 --> 00:30:54.083
Who would even join him?

00:30:54.166 --> 00:30:57.670
Mr. Kang is hard enough to deal with
as is, but what if the project fails too?

00:30:57.753 --> 00:31:00.130
Bingo. Yes, No-ah, great point.

00:31:00.214 --> 00:31:02.132
So now, what are we supposed to do?

00:31:02.216 --> 00:31:03.592
We do absolutely nothing

00:31:04.468 --> 00:31:05.594
unless we're told otherwise.

00:31:06.595 --> 00:31:10.766
Stay still and play dead.

00:31:10.849 --> 00:31:12.643
That is the answer.

00:31:12.726 --> 00:31:14.144
Okay?

00:31:15.813 --> 00:31:17.439
Mr. Kang is coming this way.

00:31:17.523 --> 00:31:19.983
Hello there! [chuckles]

00:31:23.153 --> 00:31:23.987
Oh, right.

00:31:30.494 --> 00:31:32.579
TECH NECK POSTURE
TECH NECK WARNING!

00:31:38.377 --> 00:31:40.921
He snatched my project
from right under my nose.

00:31:42.172 --> 00:31:44.925
Not a single person on this team
is allowed to apply.

00:31:45.008 --> 00:31:47.094
That would be an act of betrayal
against me.

00:31:47.177 --> 00:31:50.305
-Are we clear on that?
-[all] Yes, sir.

00:31:51.849 --> 00:31:52.850
[scoffs]

00:31:54.101 --> 00:31:55.436
[sighs]

00:31:56.687 --> 00:31:58.605
-Ms. Cha.
-Yes?

00:31:58.689 --> 00:32:00.107
How's the voice-recognition
dispenser going?

00:32:00.190 --> 00:32:02.109
We've been in the testing phase
since switching the mic.

00:32:02.693 --> 00:32:05.112
Get over there and check on it
yourself right now.

00:32:05.195 --> 00:32:08.198
If that goes wrong on top of everything
else, we are absolutely done for!

00:32:08.282 --> 00:32:09.533
Yes, sir.

00:32:10.993 --> 00:32:11.827
[Si-woo] Do you

00:32:12.661 --> 00:32:15.497
perhaps consider your current duties
to be insignificant?

00:32:17.458 --> 00:32:20.043
[Ji-yoon] Mr. Kim, I'm heading down
to check on the test.

00:32:20.127 --> 00:32:21.795
[Si-woo] Even the smallest screw

00:32:21.879 --> 00:32:24.298
can bring the whole thing down
if it's not fastened right.

00:32:24.381 --> 00:32:26.175
Please do your work
with some self-respect.

00:32:27.134 --> 00:32:28.302
Are you crying right now?

00:32:28.385 --> 00:32:30.137
[sniffles] No, I'm not.

00:32:36.018 --> 00:32:37.436
Hold it in.

00:32:37.519 --> 00:32:38.937
Crying will do you no good here.

00:32:59.249 --> 00:33:00.375
[Ji-yoon] Wow.

00:33:01.293 --> 00:33:03.212
Thank goodness I didn't join his team.

00:33:08.258 --> 00:33:09.718
TASK FORCE RECRUITMENT STATUS

00:33:09.802 --> 00:33:11.053
THERE ARE NO APPLICANTS

00:33:16.600 --> 00:33:18.560
-[commentator 1] It's a home run!
-[commentator 2 shouts]

00:33:18.644 --> 00:33:21.605
A home run!
What an unbelievable turn of events.

00:33:21.688 --> 00:33:22.981
[Ji-yoon] Hey, Buddy,

00:33:23.065 --> 00:33:24.733
give me eight ounces of cold water,
will ya?

00:33:24.817 --> 00:33:27.027
[commentator 1] The cheers of the fans
are pushing the stadium…

00:33:27.110 --> 00:33:29.029
[automated voice]
Dispensing 8 ounces of cold water.

00:33:29.112 --> 00:33:31.073
[commentator 2] That was fantastic.

00:33:31.156 --> 00:33:32.157
It worked!

00:33:33.242 --> 00:33:35.786
It's handling casual speech
and noise just fine.

00:33:35.869 --> 00:33:37.120
That's right.

00:33:37.204 --> 00:33:39.289
But how did the team even find out

00:33:39.373 --> 00:33:41.458
about this budget-friendly microphone
and recommend it?

00:33:42.042 --> 00:33:43.794
Well, it's just like you always said,

00:33:43.877 --> 00:33:45.671
the Product Planning Team

00:33:45.754 --> 00:33:48.757
should always keep some ammo
for moments like these.

00:33:48.841 --> 00:33:51.760
Mmm. So you used that extra ammo
to prepare a backup plan in advance?

00:33:51.844 --> 00:33:54.388
If I don't have a Plan B ready
ahead of time,

00:33:55.013 --> 00:33:56.265
I can't clock out early.

00:33:56.348 --> 00:33:58.517
-Exactly. Perfect answer.
-[both chuckle]

00:33:58.600 --> 00:34:02.354
Oh, I heard the ice sphere fridge
is getting a task force.

00:34:02.437 --> 00:34:03.939
Ah, yes.

00:34:04.815 --> 00:34:06.650
Oh, goodness.

00:34:06.733 --> 00:34:09.403
I knew when I saw Mr. Kang
at the Gwangju factory,

00:34:09.486 --> 00:34:11.071
that he wouldn't just let it slide.

00:34:12.114 --> 00:34:16.159
I heard that Mr. Kang actually started out
on the Development Team.

00:34:16.243 --> 00:34:17.911
What was he like when he worked there?

00:34:17.995 --> 00:34:20.956
He never smiled back then either,
barely said a word.

00:34:21.039 --> 00:34:23.375
But everyone respected him.
Say what you want,

00:34:23.458 --> 00:34:26.086
but Kang Si-woo has never
lost against a machine.

00:34:28.422 --> 00:34:29.423
Hmm.

00:34:30.841 --> 00:34:32.926
I'll, uh, let you know
when the final test results are out.

00:34:33.510 --> 00:34:34.720
Great, good luck to you.

00:34:34.803 --> 00:34:35.888
Thanks.

00:34:42.060 --> 00:34:44.104
-Mr. Ko.
-What is it?

00:34:44.897 --> 00:34:47.316
I'd like to take the day off tomorrow,
if possible.

00:34:48.901 --> 00:34:50.652
It's almost time to clock out

00:34:50.736 --> 00:34:52.487
and you want tomorrow off?

00:34:52.571 --> 00:34:54.364
Um, what nonsense is this?

00:34:55.741 --> 00:34:57.159
I'm sorry, sir.

00:34:58.201 --> 00:35:00.996
My sister had to be admitted
to the hospital all of a sudden.

00:35:01.079 --> 00:35:03.165
Wait. But why do you need
to take the day off

00:35:03.248 --> 00:35:04.958
when it's your sister
who's in the hospital?

00:35:06.418 --> 00:35:07.294
Huh?

00:35:10.255 --> 00:35:11.548
[scoffs]

00:35:11.632 --> 00:35:13.008
Times have changed so

00:35:13.550 --> 00:35:16.386
I can’t say a word
about a last-minute request like this.

00:35:17.721 --> 00:35:18.680
Do as you wish.

00:35:19.514 --> 00:35:20.682
Thank you, sir.

00:35:23.185 --> 00:35:24.394
Ms. Cha.

00:35:25.479 --> 00:35:26.605
Yes?

00:35:26.688 --> 00:35:28.899
Take over Ms. Yoon No-ah’s
overseas market research

00:35:28.982 --> 00:35:30.525
and make sure you're done by tomorrow.

00:35:30.609 --> 00:35:32.611
Oh, no, I can finish that
as soon as I'm back.

00:35:32.694 --> 00:35:33.820
It's urgent though.

00:35:33.904 --> 00:35:35.322
[sighs]

00:35:35.906 --> 00:35:37.532
Never mind then. I guess I’ll just…

00:35:37.616 --> 00:35:38.784
Understood.

00:35:38.867 --> 00:35:40.160
I will take care of it.

00:35:43.580 --> 00:35:45.999
Just send me the file,
I’ll take care of the rest for you.

00:35:46.625 --> 00:35:47.709
I'm sorry, Ms. Cha.

00:35:47.793 --> 00:35:50.420
It's all good.
He's doing that on purpose anyway.

00:35:53.173 --> 00:35:55.425
All right. Go home, everyone!

00:35:59.012 --> 00:35:59.846
OVERSEAS MARKET RESEARCH REPORT

00:35:59.930 --> 00:36:01.974
EMAIL: CHA JI-YOON

00:36:03.517 --> 00:36:05.686
No-ah, you should go.
Don’t keep your sister waiting.

00:36:06.395 --> 00:36:07.396
[sighs]

00:36:17.906 --> 00:36:20.534
[sighs] That's how it is.

00:36:21.868 --> 00:36:22.953
Love is so selfish

00:36:24.246 --> 00:36:25.664
and so foolish. [sighs]

00:36:26.873 --> 00:36:28.458
[groans]

00:36:29.960 --> 00:36:31.294
I haven't worked late in forever.

00:36:32.504 --> 00:36:33.547
[groans]

00:36:41.138 --> 00:36:43.724
[electronic voice] Good afternoon,
dear passengers.

00:36:43.807 --> 00:36:48.895
This train is a high-speed train
bound for Pohan station.

00:36:48.979 --> 00:36:51.857
-Our crew is committed to making sure…
-[sighs]

00:36:51.940 --> 00:36:54.151
…you have a comfortable journey.

00:36:54.234 --> 00:36:56.403
This train will be departing shortly.

00:36:56.486 --> 00:36:57.821
[No-ah] What time do you finish today?

00:36:57.904 --> 00:37:00.699
Late because it’s Tuesday, right?
I’m on my…

00:37:04.286 --> 00:37:07.748
WHAT TIME DO YOU GET OFF TODAY?
YOU GET OFF LATE ON TUESDAYS, RIGHT?

00:37:14.254 --> 00:37:15.589
Everything will be fine.

00:37:17.215 --> 00:37:21.053
POHAN UNIVERSITY OF SCIENCE AND TECHNOLOGY

00:37:21.136 --> 00:37:24.181
[student] Come on, Goo-won, we're not
going if you're not coming with us.

00:37:24.264 --> 00:37:26.224
-Well in that case, let me think about it.
-Right, guys?

00:37:31.980 --> 00:37:33.398
[somber music plays]

00:37:34.858 --> 00:37:36.485
Goo-won, is that someone you know?

00:37:36.568 --> 00:37:38.653
Yeah. Why don't you head out first?

00:37:43.700 --> 00:37:45.202
[sighs]

00:38:03.929 --> 00:38:05.889
You can't just come here
without telling me.

00:38:05.972 --> 00:38:06.848
Why?

00:38:07.516 --> 00:38:08.850
What? Am I not allowed to come here?

00:38:08.934 --> 00:38:11.520
No. That's not what I mean.
I told you I've been busy.

00:38:11.603 --> 00:38:12.479
Right.

00:38:12.562 --> 00:38:14.981
So busy you couldn't come to Seoul
on the weekends

00:38:15.065 --> 00:38:15.982
or reply to me?

00:38:16.066 --> 00:38:18.693
So I came to you,
is it really worth getting mad about?

00:38:19.736 --> 00:38:20.946
[sighs]

00:38:25.534 --> 00:38:26.451
I'm sorry.

00:38:27.828 --> 00:38:29.830
I mean, I just have a lot
on my plate right now.

00:38:30.455 --> 00:38:31.915
I’m a little on edge.

00:38:32.791 --> 00:38:35.710
I feel bad that you have to
come to Pohan all the time.

00:38:36.753 --> 00:38:37.587
I know you have work.

00:38:39.214 --> 00:38:41.550
I took tomorrow off
just for you to yell at me.

00:38:42.175 --> 00:38:43.009
Sorry.

00:38:43.885 --> 00:38:45.804
-Have you eaten yet?
-No.

00:38:45.887 --> 00:38:47.681
I'll treat you to something delicious.

00:38:47.764 --> 00:38:49.307
It better be delicious.

00:38:54.938 --> 00:38:56.273
[sighs]

00:39:01.528 --> 00:39:06.533
[upbeat music playing on phone]

00:39:51.870 --> 00:39:53.288
[team lead] But everyone respected him.

00:39:53.371 --> 00:39:57.417
Say what you want but Kang Si-woo
has never lost against a machine.

00:39:58.376 --> 00:40:01.087
[music continues]

00:40:30.700 --> 00:40:32.452
[sighs]

00:40:33.745 --> 00:40:36.873
That’s right a sharp… and capable boss.

00:40:38.458 --> 00:40:39.542
[sighs]

00:40:40.710 --> 00:40:42.420
The type of person I want to work for.

00:40:48.760 --> 00:40:50.178
[phone buzzing]

00:40:53.181 --> 00:40:54.474
CHO GA-EUL

00:41:00.981 --> 00:41:02.941
[tense music plays]

00:41:03.024 --> 00:41:03.858
MISSED CALL
CHO GA-EUL

00:41:09.030 --> 00:41:09.864
[Ga-eul] Ji-yoon!

00:41:14.244 --> 00:41:16.871
[soft music plays]

00:41:16.955 --> 00:41:18.331
I missed you.

00:41:21.960 --> 00:41:22.961
Why are you here?

00:41:23.545 --> 00:41:25.255
This trip was a bit too long, wasn’t it?

00:41:29.134 --> 00:41:31.136
I guess you’re pretty angry. Sorry.

00:41:31.219 --> 00:41:34.556
Isn't that something you say when you're
a few minutes late to meet someone?

00:41:35.640 --> 00:41:38.518
How could you say that
after disappearing for eight months?

00:41:38.601 --> 00:41:41.146
Did you really think
you could just say, "I'm back,"

00:41:41.229 --> 00:41:43.189
and I'd be like, "Welcome back"?

00:41:44.607 --> 00:41:46.526
-Were you waiting long?
-Yes.

00:41:46.609 --> 00:41:48.361
At first, I waited out of worry.

00:41:48.445 --> 00:41:50.739
Then I waited out of anger.

00:41:50.822 --> 00:41:53.199
And later, I waited
just so I can end things properly.

00:41:54.159 --> 00:41:57.203
I waited for you while imagining
this moment over and over again,

00:41:58.121 --> 00:42:00.165
yet you show up like it was nothing.

00:42:01.583 --> 00:42:02.876
Like it was only a couple of days.

00:42:03.460 --> 00:42:05.253
How could we break up?

00:42:05.337 --> 00:42:07.547
I can't break up with you, Ji-yoon.

00:42:08.423 --> 00:42:10.717
Let's go inside.
I have so much to tell you.

00:42:14.346 --> 00:42:15.847
I said this over text too,

00:42:15.930 --> 00:42:18.892
but I really wanted to tell you
at least once

00:42:19.768 --> 00:42:21.019
right to your face.

00:42:22.437 --> 00:42:23.730
Cho Ga-eul.

00:42:24.939 --> 00:42:26.316
It's been over between us.

00:42:27.025 --> 00:42:29.110
Ji-yoon. Ji-yoon!

00:42:29.194 --> 00:42:31.237
If you were going to do this,
why'd you come back?

00:42:31.321 --> 00:42:32.614
Tell me, what for?

00:42:35.950 --> 00:42:37.535
Because I left something important behind.

00:42:39.829 --> 00:42:41.373
And it's something I can't live without.

00:42:43.208 --> 00:42:45.126
YEAR 2021

00:42:45.210 --> 00:42:46.211
Hi there.

00:42:46.294 --> 00:42:47.295
Ga-eul.

00:42:48.463 --> 00:42:50.006
So, how have you been?

00:42:50.965 --> 00:42:53.343
[gentle music plays]

00:42:56.137 --> 00:42:58.014
[Ji-yoon]
When did you get back from Australia?

00:42:59.432 --> 00:43:00.725
I've been back for ages.

00:43:01.476 --> 00:43:04.396
I called you as soon as I got back,
but you changed your number.

00:43:04.479 --> 00:43:06.648
I changed it
when I got a new phone from work.

00:43:06.731 --> 00:43:08.817
You changed
after you started working there.

00:43:08.900 --> 00:43:11.694
We used to stay in touch
all the time before that.

00:43:15.281 --> 00:43:16.324
But we’re here,

00:43:16.908 --> 00:43:18.326
so I guess it’s all good.

00:43:20.829 --> 00:43:22.747
I guess we really are meant to be.

00:43:23.331 --> 00:43:25.250
Don't make jokes like that anymore.

00:43:27.585 --> 00:43:29.963
You know I had feelings for you
for the longest time.

00:43:31.589 --> 00:43:34.259
You don't know how hard it was
to get over you.

00:43:37.345 --> 00:43:39.013
Should we make it official then?

00:43:41.558 --> 00:43:42.434
What?

00:43:43.184 --> 00:43:45.311
Let’s make this official. Ji-yoon.

00:43:46.938 --> 00:43:47.897
Do you…

00:43:52.152 --> 00:43:53.862
Do you like me?

00:43:55.989 --> 00:43:57.073
Mm-hmm.

00:43:57.699 --> 00:43:59.284
As more than a friend though?

00:43:59.367 --> 00:44:00.201
Mm-hmm.

00:44:00.743 --> 00:44:01.953
I really like you.

00:44:02.036 --> 00:44:03.204
Since when?

00:44:04.205 --> 00:44:07.208
Between your music and your trip
to Australia, I doubt you had the time.

00:44:09.335 --> 00:44:10.670
In every spare moment.

00:44:11.171 --> 00:44:12.005
What?

00:44:12.589 --> 00:44:13.840
In the middle of work…

00:44:14.924 --> 00:44:16.468
while I was busy writing songs…

00:44:17.510 --> 00:44:19.012
even when I was just spacing out…

00:44:21.222 --> 00:44:22.765
You just kept crossing my mind,

00:44:23.766 --> 00:44:26.186
like I've left behind something important.

00:44:27.687 --> 00:44:28.897
In every spare moment…

00:44:30.190 --> 00:44:31.316
for a very long time now,

00:44:32.734 --> 00:44:35.403
I've liked you, Ji-yoon.

00:44:58.343 --> 00:45:00.011
Take it all. Everything you left behind.

00:45:00.595 --> 00:45:02.430
None of this is what I left behind.

00:45:02.514 --> 00:45:03.348
You know that.

00:45:03.932 --> 00:45:05.767
Then just throw it out for all I care.

00:45:07.685 --> 00:45:08.603
I'm sorry

00:45:09.354 --> 00:45:10.563
that it took me so long.

00:45:13.149 --> 00:45:14.234
If it took you that long…

00:45:15.401 --> 00:45:17.278
it means you’d already forgotten about me.

00:45:18.613 --> 00:45:20.031
For me, it was…

00:45:21.199 --> 00:45:22.450
a painful time,

00:45:22.534 --> 00:45:24.160
but also enough time to forget you.

00:45:26.538 --> 00:45:28.456
Don't show up
out of the blue like this again.

00:45:29.207 --> 00:45:31.000
I'm not happy to see you anymore.

00:45:32.877 --> 00:45:33.836
Ji-yoon.

00:45:35.171 --> 00:45:38.383
[somber music plays]

00:46:16.045 --> 00:46:19.132
[rain pattering]

00:46:40.737 --> 00:46:41.821
Hello.

00:46:45.325 --> 00:46:47.368
You paid
but didn't take your drink the other day.

00:46:47.452 --> 00:46:49.537
Oh, right. Well, it's all good.

00:46:49.621 --> 00:46:50.538
Did you not get it?

00:46:51.205 --> 00:46:54.000
I gave the drink to that regular of ours,
you were with.

00:46:56.169 --> 00:46:58.713
Here's the overseas market report
that Ms. Yoon No-ah was working on.

00:47:01.215 --> 00:47:04.135
This here's the profit-and-loss outlook
after replacing the microphone.

00:47:05.720 --> 00:47:06.888
[sighs]

00:47:06.971 --> 00:47:08.056
About the microphone…

00:47:08.848 --> 00:47:10.558
Use the original.

00:47:11.559 --> 00:47:12.602
What?

00:47:12.685 --> 00:47:14.729
I thought about it all night long,

00:47:14.812 --> 00:47:17.690
and replacing the microphone
just feels like a rash decision.

00:47:18.733 --> 00:47:21.486
The risk is too high.
Let's just stick to the original.

00:47:21.569 --> 00:47:23.946
But we just completed
the first round of testing.

00:47:24.697 --> 00:47:26.240
We’re supposed to start
the final round today.

00:47:26.908 --> 00:47:28.534
Then hurry over and put a stop to it.

00:47:29.702 --> 00:47:30.578
Mr. Ko.

00:47:31.204 --> 00:47:32.288
What is this?

00:47:34.874 --> 00:47:36.626
Ms. Cha, are you rebelling right now?

00:47:38.086 --> 00:47:38.961
That's not it.

00:47:40.630 --> 00:47:43.383
But there's the voice recognition issue.

00:47:43.466 --> 00:47:45.218
Tell them to stick
to the original microphone

00:47:45.301 --> 00:47:47.303
and just fix the software, will you?

00:47:47.387 --> 00:47:49.514
But doing that won’t resolve the issue.

00:47:49.597 --> 00:47:52.934
And why is that your concern though?
Are you an engineer, Ms. Cha?

00:47:53.726 --> 00:47:55.770
Just go and pass on the message.

00:47:58.189 --> 00:47:59.607
Mr. Ko, please reconsider--

00:48:02.485 --> 00:48:04.112
If you can't do it, then I'll go myself.

00:48:05.780 --> 00:48:07.907
Mr. Ko. Mr. Ko!

00:48:08.574 --> 00:48:10.618
Please reconsider this, just this once.

00:48:11.285 --> 00:48:13.830
The Development Team stayed up for days
running these tests.

00:48:13.913 --> 00:48:16.082
Yeah, and that's what those people
are there f--

00:48:16.791 --> 00:48:18.209
What the hell? Move!

00:48:18.292 --> 00:48:19.627
You haven't changed.

00:48:19.711 --> 00:48:20.586
What?

00:48:20.670 --> 00:48:23.589
I presume you had
an expensive dinner last night.

00:48:26.134 --> 00:48:28.302
[scoffs] What the…

00:48:29.345 --> 00:48:30.430
Jesus.

00:48:30.513 --> 00:48:32.390
[gentle music plays]

00:48:48.030 --> 00:48:49.323
What did you do with my drink, huh?

00:48:49.407 --> 00:48:50.658
Huh?

00:48:52.660 --> 00:48:55.872
Oh, the one from the convenience store?

00:48:55.955 --> 00:48:57.039
Did you drink it?

00:48:57.123 --> 00:48:58.458
No. It’s sitting in my fridge…

00:48:58.541 --> 00:49:00.835
Then I’ll come by and get it after work.

00:49:01.419 --> 00:49:04.130
Oh. I’ll just buy you
the exact same drink.

00:49:04.213 --> 00:49:05.298
That won’t do.

00:49:05.381 --> 00:49:07.216
Oh, then I'll bring it to you tomorrow.

00:49:07.300 --> 00:49:08.926
I have to drink that exact one today.

00:49:12.597 --> 00:49:13.431
Okay.

00:49:31.616 --> 00:49:35.036
You do know
that was unreasonable, don't you?

00:49:35.119 --> 00:49:36.120
[chuckles]

00:49:37.914 --> 00:49:40.082
You would've just avoided me
if I'd asked to meet.

00:49:43.377 --> 00:49:45.129
What happened after? With Mr. Ko?

00:49:45.213 --> 00:49:48.132
The Development Team
went completely ballistic.

00:49:48.841 --> 00:49:52.762
Then… everything returned to normal,
like nothing happened.

00:49:55.389 --> 00:49:57.475
[Si-woo sighs]

00:50:00.019 --> 00:50:01.270
Something similar happened

00:50:02.021 --> 00:50:03.481
when I was a Sr. Associate.

00:50:04.690 --> 00:50:06.234
Mr. Ko was the team lead,

00:50:06.818 --> 00:50:10.321
and he insisted on replacing a capable
part with one from a different supplier.

00:50:10.404 --> 00:50:11.572
I looked into it

00:50:12.865 --> 00:50:14.909
and found out
that he’d been taking favors.

00:50:16.911 --> 00:50:18.996
Get this, Kang Si-woo
was a senior associate

00:50:19.080 --> 00:50:22.834
and he reported his team lead,
Mr. Ko, for taking bribes.

00:50:22.917 --> 00:50:25.169
-[gasps]
-Just so he could take that spot.

00:50:25.837 --> 00:50:27.922
So then what did you end up doing?

00:50:28.005 --> 00:50:30.007
I reported it to the Audit Team.

00:50:30.758 --> 00:50:32.301
But without conclusive evidence,

00:50:33.010 --> 00:50:35.805
they just kept the original supplier
and closed the case.

00:50:36.597 --> 00:50:39.809
And then I just got kicked off
of the Product Planning Team.

00:50:43.771 --> 00:50:45.815
That must have been really hard.

00:50:45.898 --> 00:50:47.108
That's when I made up my mind.

00:50:48.192 --> 00:50:50.820
I’d stay out of it all
and just let my work speak for itself.

00:50:53.281 --> 00:50:54.323
Join my task force.

00:50:54.949 --> 00:50:57.076
I’ll make sure
you never have to deal with that again.

00:50:57.994 --> 00:50:59.954
Why are you doing all this for me?

00:51:00.997 --> 00:51:02.957
We haven't even
known each other that long.

00:51:05.293 --> 00:51:06.377
I've been watching you

00:51:08.087 --> 00:51:09.380
for quite some time.

00:51:09.463 --> 00:51:13.009
[pop music plays]

00:51:16.095 --> 00:51:17.138
Hello, everyone!

00:51:17.221 --> 00:51:18.639
My name is Cha Ji-yoon.

00:51:18.723 --> 00:51:20.057
[cheers]

00:51:20.141 --> 00:51:24.228
One day, I want to create
an automated Snail Bride homemaker system

00:51:24.312 --> 00:51:27.565
that takes care of the cleaning,
laundry and dishes

00:51:27.648 --> 00:51:28.691
all on its own!

00:51:28.774 --> 00:51:30.902
SAEUM NEW HIRE ORIENTATION

00:51:30.985 --> 00:51:32.028
What's your ultimate goal?

00:51:32.111 --> 00:51:35.281
Obviously, my ultimate goal
is becoming the president of SAEUM.

00:51:35.364 --> 00:51:37.909
[all cheering]

00:51:39.243 --> 00:51:42.204
[Si-woo] I found one new hire’s
ambitious goal to be quite impressive.

00:51:43.080 --> 00:51:45.041
Still, I assumed it wouldn’t last long,

00:51:45.124 --> 00:51:47.043
just like with any other rookie.

00:51:47.126 --> 00:51:50.129
[Ji-yoon] What if there were
a talking companion robot vacuum?

00:51:50.212 --> 00:51:53.591
If you combine a robot vacuum cleaner
with a voice assistant service,

00:51:53.674 --> 00:51:55.968
it can evolve into a talking robot vacuum.

00:51:56.052 --> 00:51:58.512
Users could give it
a name of their choice,

00:51:58.596 --> 00:52:01.057
and whenever they have a question
or just need someone to talk to,

00:52:01.140 --> 00:52:03.351
they could chat with their vacuum.

00:52:04.018 --> 00:52:06.854
"Ms. Bokja,
will it stop raining tomorrow?"

00:52:08.105 --> 00:52:10.942
Uh, maybe Ms. Bokja is a little tacky.

00:52:11.025 --> 00:52:12.985
[Si-woo] But that rookie was different.

00:52:13.069 --> 00:52:15.863
She knew exactly what she wanted
right from the very beginning.

00:52:17.490 --> 00:52:18.324
Enough already.

00:52:18.407 --> 00:52:19.408
I know it's a machine,

00:52:19.492 --> 00:52:21.619
but it has to feel
like it has real emotions.

00:52:26.290 --> 00:52:27.208
Huh?

00:52:31.045 --> 00:52:33.798
[Si-woo] Even as she gained seniority,
she refused to compromise,

00:52:33.881 --> 00:52:35.841
and I found myself rooting for her.

00:52:37.426 --> 00:52:39.971
But when I saw you again at the factory,

00:52:40.054 --> 00:52:41.263
you'd changed a lot.

00:52:41.347 --> 00:52:44.058
And then we can gradually work on
perfecting the ice quality from there?

00:52:44.141 --> 00:52:47.061
To be honest, I was disappointed.

00:52:47.687 --> 00:52:51.232
But then I saw your notebook and realized.

00:52:51.899 --> 00:52:53.025
You hadn't changed.

00:52:54.318 --> 00:52:55.695
You were just hiding.

00:52:55.778 --> 00:52:58.447
And then I thought to myself,
"I don't want to let this person go."

00:53:00.116 --> 00:53:02.535
The way I see it… you deserve

00:53:02.618 --> 00:53:05.788
to aim a lot higher
than what you have so far.

00:53:05.871 --> 00:53:07.915
It would be a real shame to keep all that

00:53:08.541 --> 00:53:11.168
potential locked away in a notebook.

00:53:11.252 --> 00:53:13.838
[gentle music plays]

00:53:13.921 --> 00:53:15.172
I'll give you time to think.

00:53:18.217 --> 00:53:19.385
As for my drink,

00:53:20.177 --> 00:53:21.512
thank you for holding on to it.

00:53:34.066 --> 00:53:34.900
What?

00:53:38.070 --> 00:53:39.530
Those words, make me…

00:53:41.824 --> 00:53:44.785
feel… I feel… giddy.

00:54:07.183 --> 00:54:09.602
[scoffs] She must've run here.

00:54:22.907 --> 00:54:25.743
[No-ah] Babe, should I move down here
once we’re married?

00:54:26.827 --> 00:54:28.079
[Goo-won] What about your job?

00:54:28.662 --> 00:54:30.289
Well, I could find a job here

00:54:30.372 --> 00:54:31.791
and maybe go into the public-sector.

00:54:32.750 --> 00:54:35.294
Come on, why would you leave
a big company everyone's

00:54:35.377 --> 00:54:36.754
dying to get into?

00:54:37.755 --> 00:54:40.758
Even after you get your degree,
you won’t be able to come to Seoul.

00:54:40.841 --> 00:54:43.969
What's the point of getting married
if we still can't see each other often?

00:54:47.473 --> 00:54:48.933
[clears throat]

00:54:49.016 --> 00:54:50.518
You’re gonna be late to class
because of me.

00:54:50.601 --> 00:54:52.061
You should get going.

00:54:52.853 --> 00:54:54.021
Mm-hmm.

00:54:54.605 --> 00:54:55.564
Bye then.

00:55:01.821 --> 00:55:02.780
No-ah!

00:55:06.534 --> 00:55:07.535
No-ah, let's just…

00:55:07.618 --> 00:55:12.790
[electronic voice] Attention, passengers.
The 559 train bound for Seoul

00:55:12.873 --> 00:55:13.999
is now arriving at Platform 7.

00:55:14.083 --> 00:55:15.417
-[train horn blares]
-…break up.

00:55:15.501 --> 00:55:18.003
[electronic voice]
Please stand behind the yellow line.

00:55:18.087 --> 00:55:22.758
Passengers, please check your boarding
position before stepping onto the train.

00:55:22.842 --> 00:55:24.260
Enjoy your trip.

00:55:26.053 --> 00:55:30.516
[sad music plays]

00:55:47.408 --> 00:55:48.826
[breathing shakily]

00:55:49.577 --> 00:55:50.619
[gasps] No-ah!

00:55:51.453 --> 00:55:52.329
What's wrong?

00:55:52.413 --> 00:55:53.789
Oh, my gosh.

00:55:53.873 --> 00:55:54.790
Are you sick?

00:55:55.374 --> 00:55:56.542
Ms. Cha…

00:55:56.625 --> 00:55:57.960
Let's get you to the hospital. Get up.

00:55:58.878 --> 00:56:01.589
I can't. I already took yesterday off.

00:56:01.672 --> 00:56:04.091
You can't work in this state, okay.

00:56:05.843 --> 00:56:08.888
What? Taking the day off yesterday

00:56:08.971 --> 00:56:10.181
and you’re leaving early today?

00:56:11.473 --> 00:56:13.601
I make sure to only get sick after work

00:56:13.684 --> 00:56:15.144
and on weekends.

00:56:15.227 --> 00:56:17.563
Taking care of yourself
is part of the job!

00:56:19.231 --> 00:56:20.149
Ms. Yoon No-ah.

00:56:22.651 --> 00:56:23.485
Mr. Ko.

00:56:23.569 --> 00:56:26.405
Ms. Yoon No-ah, what exactly
are your strengths?

00:56:26.488 --> 00:56:27.656
Huh?

00:56:27.740 --> 00:56:29.366
You’re not a fast worker like Ms. Cha.

00:56:29.450 --> 00:56:30.826
And you don't have any guts either!

00:56:30.910 --> 00:56:33.245
Ms. No-ah is very unwell at the moment.

00:56:33.329 --> 00:56:35.789
Let her go home for now
and you can speak to her again tomorrow.

00:56:35.873 --> 00:56:38.876
Seeing as you’re in the same outfit
as the other day,

00:56:39.585 --> 00:56:41.295
it seems you lied
about your sister being sick

00:56:41.378 --> 00:56:43.172
and went on vacation with your boyfriend.

00:56:43.255 --> 00:56:46.300
-Mr. Ko!
-Why don't you get married already?

00:56:46.383 --> 00:56:48.719
Stop wasting everyone’s time,
showing up to just collect a paycheck!

00:56:48.802 --> 00:56:50.721
Please just stop this!

00:56:55.851 --> 00:56:57.186
Diminishing or mocking

00:56:57.269 --> 00:56:59.730
an employee’s performance or abilities
without a proper reason.

00:57:00.689 --> 00:57:03.734
Pressuring them not to use their vacation,
or their sick leave

00:57:04.652 --> 00:57:07.029
and spreading gossip or rumors
about their personal life.

00:57:07.947 --> 00:57:11.033
Every single word you just said
to Ms. Yoon No-ah,

00:57:11.659 --> 00:57:13.494
constitutes workplace harassment.

00:57:14.078 --> 00:57:15.120
[Young-sam scoffs]

00:57:15.746 --> 00:57:17.623
Are you saying you’ll report me
or something?

00:57:17.706 --> 00:57:19.375
I really don’t want to do that.

00:57:20.960 --> 00:57:22.461
So I ask you to please…

00:57:23.921 --> 00:57:26.423
stop speaking to us so disrespectfully
from now on.

00:57:30.052 --> 00:57:31.136
I ask you kindly.

00:57:39.937 --> 00:57:41.605
I didn’t expect this from you,

00:57:42.523 --> 00:57:43.399
Ms. Cha.

00:57:44.441 --> 00:57:45.776
[exhales sharply]

00:57:47.486 --> 00:57:48.445
Fine.

00:57:49.238 --> 00:57:50.531
Let's do that.

00:57:50.614 --> 00:57:51.615
Going forward,

00:57:51.699 --> 00:57:54.910
I will be very polite to
each and every one of you.

00:57:55.494 --> 00:57:56.495
Oh.

00:57:57.288 --> 00:58:00.457
Ms. Yoon No-ah, since you're feeling sick,
you may leave early.

00:58:02.001 --> 00:58:03.085
And Ms. Cha Ji-yoon.

00:58:04.837 --> 00:58:06.505
Please analyze our competitors’ trends

00:58:06.588 --> 00:58:09.258
over the last three years
and prepare a report for me.

00:58:10.217 --> 00:58:12.177
This is not an unfair assignment,

00:58:12.261 --> 00:58:16.682
but a perfectly legitimate request
that is completely necessary for the team.

00:58:25.190 --> 00:58:26.650
What are you staring at exactly?

00:58:42.416 --> 00:58:44.251
Why would you pick a fight with him?

00:58:44.335 --> 00:58:45.294
Ms. Cha.

00:58:46.545 --> 00:58:47.421
[Ji-yoon] Let's go.

00:58:50.132 --> 00:58:51.675
-[whimpers]
-Go straight to the hospital.

00:58:51.759 --> 00:58:53.969
I can't come with you,
so call your sister.

00:58:54.678 --> 00:58:56.722
I'm sorry. It's all my fault.

00:58:56.805 --> 00:58:59.516
It's not your fault. Get going now.

00:59:09.526 --> 00:59:12.279
[breathes shakily]

00:59:23.749 --> 00:59:25.751
[lighthearted music plays]

00:59:39.139 --> 00:59:40.641
PRODUCT PLANNING TEAM 1
CHA JI-YOON

00:59:41.809 --> 00:59:42.810
[sighs]

00:59:47.689 --> 00:59:49.400
Hi, Mom! [chuckles]

00:59:49.483 --> 00:59:51.568
I'm officially starting work tomorrow!

00:59:51.652 --> 00:59:53.695
I've been assigned
to the Product Planning Team.

00:59:53.779 --> 00:59:56.824
My name and face are right here
on my employee ID! [chuckles]

00:59:56.907 --> 00:59:59.118
[Mom] I'm actually at the shop right now
to buy rice cakes

00:59:59.201 --> 01:00:00.661
for the whole neighborhood.

01:00:01.328 --> 01:00:03.122
What? Why would you buy that?

01:00:03.205 --> 01:00:06.500
[Mom] My daughter got a job at a major
corporation, so it’s the least I can do.

01:00:06.583 --> 01:00:08.377
So what is this product team?

01:00:08.460 --> 01:00:10.003
What will you be doing there?

01:00:10.087 --> 01:00:12.089
You wouldn't know even if I told you.

01:00:12.172 --> 01:00:15.926
I'm going to work so hard, you know?

01:00:16.009 --> 01:00:19.096
Actually, I’m just going to work
in this place forever and ever.

01:00:19.179 --> 01:00:21.515
[chuckles] I’m heading home now.

01:00:21.598 --> 01:00:22.683
Let’s have a party tonight.

01:00:56.967 --> 01:00:59.470
COMPETITOR TRENDS REPORT, 2023-2025

01:01:06.185 --> 01:01:08.687
[Ji-yoon] Product Planning Team 1.
Cha Ji-yoon.

01:01:08.770 --> 01:01:11.273
Rank: Senior Associate.

01:01:11.356 --> 01:01:13.358
I hereby submit my resignation
for personal reasons…

01:01:13.442 --> 01:01:14.276
RESIGNATION URGE STICKERS

01:01:14.860 --> 01:01:17.571
…so I ask that it be processed…

01:01:21.575 --> 01:01:23.035
LETTER OF RESIGNATION

01:01:23.118 --> 01:01:24.703
"Personal reasons," my ass.

01:01:25.621 --> 01:01:27.080
You all probably look at me,

01:01:27.164 --> 01:01:30.584
and see nothing
but a lowly corporate slave.

01:01:30.667 --> 01:01:32.461
But I want you to know

01:01:32.544 --> 01:01:36.465
that I was once a bright-eyed,
passionate employee

01:01:37.216 --> 01:01:43.722
who walked through those doors
full of hopes and wonderful dreams.

01:01:43.805 --> 01:01:46.767
Does it make you feel good
to insult my character?

01:01:46.850 --> 01:01:49.853
To look down on me
and treat me like trash?

01:01:49.937 --> 01:01:52.189
This place is toxic and pathetic.

01:01:52.272 --> 01:01:56.151
[scoffs] I am walking out of here
on my own terms, everyone.

01:01:56.235 --> 01:02:00.239
Have a nice life. As for me,
I'm off to find my happiness.

01:02:00.322 --> 01:02:02.241
LETTER OF RESIGNATION
CONFIRM SUBMISSION

01:02:06.995 --> 01:02:08.664
SUBMIT THIS DOCUMENT?
CANCEL - CONFIRM

01:02:13.710 --> 01:02:15.045
[sighs] Damn it.

01:02:17.673 --> 01:02:18.882
[sighs]

01:02:28.100 --> 01:02:31.478
How sad and pathetic can you really be?
Huh?

01:02:31.562 --> 01:02:33.605
[sighs] I couldn’t even throw these away.

01:02:49.329 --> 01:02:50.539
[sighs]

01:03:16.565 --> 01:03:20.027
HOT AIR UV SYSTEM
SHOE CARE DEVICE

01:03:20.110 --> 01:03:21.612
[Si-woo] I’m here from the future.

01:03:21.695 --> 01:03:22.821
This has already been released.

01:03:40.422 --> 01:03:42.299
[Ji-yoon]
Washer and dryer combined into one?

01:03:42.883 --> 01:03:44.760
[Si-woo]
Now it's possible with a single machine.

01:03:45.677 --> 01:03:46.803
[Ji-yoon] How should I open this?

01:03:47.929 --> 01:03:50.140
[Si-woo]
Touch lightly to automatically open doors.

01:03:51.350 --> 01:03:54.144
Why did he have to go scribble
all over someone else's notebook?

01:03:54.227 --> 01:03:56.104
[gentle music plays]

01:03:56.980 --> 01:03:58.899
Did he think using a pencil was okay?

01:04:02.653 --> 01:04:05.781
Can't we turn everything into away mode,
like with a hotel key card?

01:04:06.531 --> 01:04:07.658
[Si-woo] It's possible.

01:04:07.741 --> 01:04:11.536
You just design a single software
to control multiple hardware devices,

01:04:11.620 --> 01:04:15.457
like using a single smartphone
to control all your home appliances.

01:04:20.962 --> 01:04:22.422
[Ji-yoon] Ice spikes?

01:04:29.805 --> 01:04:30.639
[Si-woo] Good!

01:04:31.223 --> 01:04:32.474
[cries]

01:04:33.558 --> 01:04:34.726
Mr. Kang…

01:04:36.436 --> 01:04:37.896
He’s seriously the worst.

01:04:49.741 --> 01:04:51.243
[inspirational music plays]

01:05:03.588 --> 01:05:05.632
LETTER OF RESIGNATION
SUBMIT THIS DOCUMENT?

01:05:20.564 --> 01:05:22.774
SUBMIT THIS DOCUMENT?
CANCEL - CONFIRM

01:05:30.449 --> 01:05:32.325
[Ji-yoon]
There's no such thing as the perfect boss.

01:05:34.870 --> 01:05:36.872
Just like there isn't a perfect lover.

01:05:39.875 --> 01:05:41.418
-Good morning.
-Good morning.

01:05:41.501 --> 01:05:43.128
[upbeat music plays]

01:05:43.211 --> 01:05:47.883
Just wear a pair of acupressure slippers,
and it'll solve everything.

01:05:49.259 --> 01:05:50.719
Oh.

01:05:50.802 --> 01:05:52.012
Good morning, Mr. Ko. Everything good?

01:05:52.095 --> 01:05:54.014
Mm-hmm. Good morning, Ms. Cha.

01:06:00.270 --> 01:06:01.271
What the…

01:06:01.354 --> 01:06:03.899
[Ji-yoon] At the end of the day,
this is just a game of this or that.

01:06:03.982 --> 01:06:06.151
[Young-sam] Why are you going that way?
Wrong way. Huh?

01:06:06.234 --> 01:06:07.277
Huh?

01:06:07.360 --> 01:06:10.280
[Ji-yoon] Even if tomorrow's me
regrets the choices I make today…

01:06:10.864 --> 01:06:12.032
[employee] What?

01:06:12.115 --> 01:06:15.577
Sr. Associate Cha Ji-yoon, checking in.
I’d like to apply for the task force.

01:06:18.079 --> 01:06:19.080
[Young-sam] Hey!

01:06:22.542 --> 01:06:24.336
[Ji-yoon] All I can do is choose
the lesser

01:06:24.419 --> 01:06:26.588
evil, instead of the absolute worst.

01:06:30.509 --> 01:06:31.510
I look forward to this.

01:06:35.514 --> 01:06:36.765
I look forward to it too.

01:06:36.848 --> 01:06:39.184
[theme music playing]

01:07:29.985 --> 01:07:33.738
With the time we have left, we have
to be able to make the perfect ice sphere.

01:07:33.822 --> 01:07:35.991
-Would that be possible?
-Fail. Fail.

01:07:36.074 --> 01:07:37.617
-[groans]
-[sighs]

01:07:37.701 --> 01:07:39.035
I'm wiped.

01:07:41.413 --> 01:07:43.081
[Si-woo] Please change your keyboard
to a silent keyboard.

01:07:43.164 --> 01:07:45.917
[Ji-yoon] I'll clock out on time
no matter what and order fried chicken.

01:07:46.001 --> 01:07:47.711
This is awkward as hell.

01:07:48.753 --> 01:07:51.506
[Ga-eul] I’m finally done
composing our song.

01:07:52.632 --> 01:07:54.843
Would you mind leaving us?

01:07:55.468 --> 01:07:56.845
I have something to tell her.

01:07:56.928 --> 01:07:59.222
So I assume you’ll be free this weekend.

01:07:59.306 --> 01:08:00.932
[Ji-yoon] Lovesick, really?